  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      160 children (based on the inclusion and exclusion criteria described above) admitted in PICU&#xD;
      will be daily assessed by two nurses (inter-evaluator agreement) using the Italian version of&#xD;
      CAPD scale administered twice at a distance of 2 minutes (intra-evaluator agreement).&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The psychometric validation study will take place in the PICU of the Hospital of Padua. CAPD&#xD;
      translation and cultural adaptation was developed within the Pediatric Cardiac Surgery&#xD;
      Intensive Care Unit of the Federico II Polyclinic.&#xD;
&#xD;
      In this study we aim to perform the psychometric validation. 160 children (based on the&#xD;
      inclusion and exclusion criteria described above) admitted in PICU will be daily assessed by&#xD;
      two nurses (inter-evaluator agreement) using the Italian version of CAPD scale administered&#xD;
      twice at a distance of 2 minutes (intra-evaluator agreement).&#xD;
&#xD;
      The score will be recorded in a data collection card, all the cards will be collected and&#xD;
      then analyzed.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
